summary: I fully believe that during the, at minimum, weeks that it took to clean up winterfell Arya and Gendry spent almost all of their...
body:
I fully believe that during the, at minimum, weeks that it took to clean up winterfell Arya and Gendry spent almost all of their time together and definitely spent their nights together, which is why he was looking for her so much at the feast and why they were so comfortable and soft with each other and why he thought, with the help of alcohol, proposing was the smart move because they had a real and beautiful relationship and all he really knew about lords and ladies is that they get married and now that he was a lord and they were banging all the time and they were in love (they were definitely both in love) he thought that was the appropriate thing to do since they were always together anyway and society couldn’t stop them anymore

Literally the only problem was that he used the wrong words and she still needed to work through her revenge plans and ptsd so she thought that letting him down based only on titles (she never actually said no to the proposal) would be better for him rather than her dying on her revenge quest and him mourning the life they were going to have together (also he definitely would have tried to come with her)

So basically what I’m saying is that they had a long and meaningful romantic relationship in which they did end up secretly getting married we just didn’t get to see most of it, but they 100% did end up together

body:
Gendrya Prompt

For all you fanfic authors out here:

First of all, let me tell you how grateful I am that you’ve created something to sustain me and others with the wonderful writings to see us through these dark times. I tip my hat to you…

Secondly, I have a request. Since I’m shit at writing, I’d like to propose a scenario for those of you interested. *a-hem*

A fic of our two babes meeting again at King’s Landing before Arya sets sail. Mostly, how they talk and clear the air. What I really want, is them deciding to get married in secret and Gendry telling her to go and have her adventures and that he’ll wait for her in Storm’s End for when she comes back and she can be whatever lady she wants to be. And how he’d never ask her to fulfill traditional lady duties anyway because that’s not why he loves her (because apparently D & D “forgot” about that part of their characters 🙄).

I think may have happened (in my head canon anyway), since the markings on his clothing are indicative of wolf claw marks, and she wears the Baratheon colors as she sets sail and puts her hair up, not leaving it down like a maiden would.

So, if any one of you lovelies would be interested in perhaps tackling such a story, I look forward to reading it. It can be more than one, I’m not picky. My AO3 username is the same as it is here, snapdragon76.


Spread more of that Gendrya love!!!

summary:
@teenwolfpineapple requested Ser Family parent/teacher conferences so here ya go! 
Sansa's teacher: Your daughter is truly a...
body:
@teenwolfpineapple requested Ser Family parent/teacher conferences so here ya go!

Sansa’s teacher: Your daughter is truly a delight but…she can be a bit too opinionated.

Jaime: What’s wrong with being opinionated? Huh?? If she were a boy would you be saying she’s “opinionated”?

Brienne: If she were a boy she’d be “a leader” right?

Jaime: In the words of my daughter, we stan one (1)-

Brienne, whispering to Jaime: Three.

Jaime: Sorry sorry. We stan THREE opinionated daughters in OUR household.

~

Bran’s teacher: Your son is very intelligent but…he’s a bit…weird.

Jaime: WEIRD AF

Brienne: And don’t you forget it!!

Jaime: Let my boy’s freak flag fly!!!

Brienne, whispering to Jaime: Jaime, I don’t think freak flag is the right term.

Jaime: Whatever. You know what I mean.

Jaime: Call our boy weird again and catch these HANDS!

~

Gendry’s teacher: Your son is 17, he can’t read, and he likes to buck authority.

Jaime and Brienne: *nodding*

Gendry’s teacher: Do you have anything to say to that?

Brienne: Nope.

Jaime: It be like that sometimes.

~

Arya’s teacher: Your daughter is a nightmare.

Jaime: *smiling* But she’s our nightmare.

Brienne: *proudly* Yep.

~

Pod’s teacher: Your son is truly a delight but…he just gets too emotional sometimes.

Jaime: ARE YOU SAYING-

Brienne: Jaime, please stay calm-

Jaime: I WILL NOT

Jaime: ARE YOU SAYING BOYS CAN’T CRY?!?

Teacher: No…I-

Jaime: I CRY AT LEAST 20 TIMES A DAY!

Brienne: It’s true.

Jaime: I’LL CRY RIGHT FUCKING NOW

Teacher: Sir, please don-

Jaime: *wailing*

Brienne: What he’s trying to say is Pod feels things very deeply and if he wants to cry you better DAMN WELL LET HIM!

Jaime: In the words of my daughter, we stan one (1)-

Brienne, whispering to Jaime: Three.

Jaime: Sorry sorry. We stan THREE opinionated daughters in OUR household.

~

Bran’s teacher: Your son is very intelligent but…he’s a bit…weird.

Jaime: WEIRD AF

Brienne: And don’t you forget it!!

Jaime: Let my boy’s freak flag fly!!!

Brienne, whispering to Jaime: Jaime, I don’t think freak flag is the right term.

Jaime: Whatever. You know what I mean.

Jaime: Call our boy weird again and catch these HANDS!

~

Gendry’s teacher: Your son is 17, he can’t read, and he likes to buck authority.

Jaime and Brienne: *nodding*

Gendry’s teacher: Do you have anything to say to that?

Brienne: Nope.

Jaime: It be like that sometimes.

~

Arya’s teacher: Your daughter is a nightmare.

Jaime: *smiling* But she’s our nightmare.

Brienne: *proudly* Yep.

~

Pod’s teacher: Your son is truly a delight but…he just gets too emotional sometimes.

Jaime: ARE YOU SAYING-

Brienne: Jaime, please stay calm-

Jaime: I WILL NOT

Jaime: ARE YOU SAYING BOYS CAN’T CRY?!?

Teacher: No…I-

Jaime: I CRY AT LEAST 20 TIMES A DAY!

Brienne: It’s true.

Jaime: I’LL CRY RIGHT FUCKING NOW

Teacher: Sir, please don-

Jaime: *wailing*

Brienne: What he’s trying to say is Pod feels things very deeply and if he wants to cry you better DAMN WELL LET HIM!
